Description: Our contractors Avidety Ltd are replacing and upgrading electricity poles due to them decaying in and around Blacketts Road. This will improve the reliability of the electricity network and reduce the risk of you having an unplanned power cut. During this time you will be connected to a generator to provide you electricity whilst we carry out our essential works. In order to connect and disconnect the generator we will need to temporarily switch off your power. The government has given exemptions to certain industries and activities, this outage falls into this category. We aim to connect and disconnect the generator as soon as possible so your power may come on sooner.

There is a power cut in the FK7 postcode area of Stirling. It has been necessary for our engineers to carry out an emergency shutdown at 12:30pm due to an underground cable fault on Bandeath Road and this may affect the supply to your property. We will work to get your power back on as quickly and as safely as possible by 3:30pm. We will update this message if this information changes. We apologise for the inconvenience and thank you for your patience. This message was updated at 12:17pm on Thursday, 22 April 2021

The electricity supply to your premises may currently be affected by planned work.  You should have received a letter explaining this.  We hope to be able to restore your supplies by 22-APR-2021 14:00.  Please accept our sincere apologies for any inconvenience this is causing.

*Please note that this is the planned power cut that was postponed from the 9th of April.* Our contractors Avidety Ltd are replacing and upgrading electricity poles due to them decaying outside numbers 14, 15 & 18 Mountain Street. This will improve the reliability of the electricity network and will reduce the risk of you having an unplanned power cut which is why it is important to complete this work during the Coronavirus pandemic. You may see our contractors completing preparation works prior to the outage to allow for a shorter interruption on the day of the planned power cut. The government has given exemptions to certain industries and activities, this outage falls into this category. We are sorry for any inconvenience caused by this work and thank you for your patience.
